com.googlecode.cqengine.index.navigable

Class NavigableIndex<A extends Comparable<A>,O>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.googlecode.cqengine.index.common.AbstractAttributeIndex<A,O>
      • com.googlecode.cqengine.index.common.AbstractMapBasedAttributeIndex<A,O>
        • com.googlecode.cqengine.index.navigable.NavigableIndex<A,O>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ModificationListener<O>, AttributeIndex<A,O>, Index<O>

    public class NavigableIndex<A extends Comparable<A>,O>
extends AbstractMapBasedAttributeIndex<A,O>
    An index backed by a ConcurrentSkipListMap.

    Supports query types:

    • Equal
    • LessThan
    • GreaterThan
    • Between
    Author:
    Niall Gallagher

      • retrieve

        public ResultSet<O> retrieve(Query<O> query,
                    Map<Class<? extends QueryOption>,QueryOption<O>> queryOptions)
        Returns a ResultSet which when iterated will return objects from the index matching the query supplied.

        Usually ResultSets are lazy which means that they don't actually do any work, or encapsulate or materialize matching objects, but rather they encapsulate logic to fetch matching objects from the index on-the-fly as the application iterates through the ResultSet.

        Parameters:
        query - An object which specifies some restriction on an attribute of an object
        queryOptions - A map of QueryOption class to QueryOption object containing optional parameters for the query
        Returns:
        A set of objects with attributes matching the restriction imposed by the query
        See Also:
        #supportsQuery(com.googlecode.cqengine.query.Query

      • filterForQuantization

        protected ResultSet<O> filterForQuantization(ResultSet<O> storedResultSet,
                                 Query<O> query)
        A no-op method which can be overridden by a subclass to return a ResultSet which filters objects from the given ResultSet, to return only those objects matching the query, for the case that the index is using a Quantizer.

        This default implementation simply returns the given ResultSet unmodified.

        Parameters:
        storedResultSet - A ResultSet stored against a quantized key in the index
        query - The query against which results should be matched
        Returns:
        A ResultSet which filters objects from the given ResultSet, to return only those objects matching the query

      • onAttribute

        public static <A extends Comparable<A>,O> NavigableIndex<A,O> onAttribute(Attribute<O,A> attribute)
        Creates a new NavigableIndex on the given attribute. The attribute can be a SimpleAttribute or a MultiValueAttribute, as long as the type of the attribute referenced implements Comparable.

        Type Parameters:
        A - The type of the attribute
        O - The type of the object containing the attribute
        Parameters:
        attribute - The attribute on which the index will be built, a SimpleAttribute or a MultiValueAttribute where the type of the attribute referenced implements Comparable
        Returns:
        A new HashIndex which will build an index on this attribute
